=I've created a {{ $json.InitialUserInput.slides }}-slide image carousel about '{{ $json.InitialUserInput.topic }}' in a '{{ $json.InitialUserInput.style }}' style.
The general themes of the slides are:
{{ $json.PromptsArray.map(p => "- " + p.split("Overlay caption:")[0].trim()).slice(0, 3).join('\n') }}
{{ $json.PromptsArray.length > 3 ? "\n- ...and more." : "" }}

Please generate a single, short, and engaging caption for this carousel, suitable for Instagram and TikTok. The caption MUST be 90 characters or less. Do not include hashtags. Respond only with the caption itself.

parameters.jsCode:
// The input 'items[0]' contains:
// - items[0].json: { PromptsArray, LoopIndex: 0, GeneratedPhotosBinaries: {}, CurrentImageKeyForNextEdit: "image_for_edit", InitialUserInput }
// - items[0].binary.data: The binary data of the first generated image

const newItem = items[0];
const firstImageBinary = newItem.binary.data; // Get the binary from "Convert to File 1"

// 1. Determine the key for this first photo (e.g., "photo1")
// LoopIndex is currently 0, so LoopIndex + 1 is 1.
const photoKey = "photo" + (newItem.json.LoopIndex + 1);

// 2. Store this first image's binary into the GeneratedPhotosBinaries object
newItem.json.GeneratedPhotosBinaries[photoKey] = firstImageBinary;

// 3. Make this image's binary available under the key specified by CurrentImageKeyForNextEdit.
// This key ("image_for_edit") will be used as the input for the *first iteration* of the edit loop.
newItem.binary[newItem.json.CurrentImageKeyForNextEdit] = firstImageBinary;

// 4. Increment LoopIndex. It will now be 1, ready for processing the second prompt (PromptsArray[1]).
newItem.json.LoopIndex++;

// 5. Clean up the original 'binary.data' property from "Convert to File 1"
// as we've now stored its content under more specific keys.
// This helps keep the item's binary data organized.
delete newItem.binary.data;

// Return the modified item, which now contains the processed first image
// and updated loop variables.
return newItem;

